name: Bob Baxter
studentBio: Bob Baxter attended Pelican Lake Residential School at Sioux Lookout, Ontario, which was open from 1927 to 1978 and operaed by the Anglican Church. He gave a statement to the Truth and Reconciliation Commision on 24 November, 2010 in Thunder Bay, Ontario.

name: Albert Elias
studentBio: Albert Elias attended All Saints Residential School in Aklavik, Northwest Territories from approximately 1952-1955. The school was run by the Anglican Church. He gave a statement to the Truth and Reconciliation Commission on 1 July 2011 in Inuvik, Northwest Territories.

name: Lynda Pahpasay McDonald
studentBio: Lynda Pahpasay McDonald attended St. Mary's, a Roman Catholic residential school, in Kenora, Ontario in the 1950s, starting when she was four years old. She gave a statement to the Truth and Reconciliation Commission on 16 June 2010 in Winnipeg, Manitoba.

name: Mabel Brown
studentBio: Mabel Brown attended Akaitcho Hall, also known as Yellowknife Federal Hostel, in Yellowknife, Northwest Territories. The school was operated by the federal government and was open from 1958 until 1994. Mabel gave a statement to the Truth and Reconciliation Commission on 28 September 2011 in Inuvik, Northwest Territories.

name: Emily Kematch
studentBio: Emily Kematch attended Gordon's Residential School in Punichy, Saskatchewan, one of the longest operating schools and operated by the Anglican Church. She came from York Landing in Northern Manitoba. Emily gave a statement to the Truth and Reconciliation Commission on 18 June 2010 in Winnipeg, Manitoba.

name: Anthony Henry
studentBio: Lynda Pahpasay McDonald attended St. Mary's, a Roman Catholic residential school, in Kenora, Ontario in the 1950s, starting when she was four years old. She gave a statement to the Truth and Reconciliation Commission on 16 June 2010 in Winnipeg, Manitoba.

name: Albert Fiddler
studentBio: Albert Fiddler attended Beauval Residential School, also known as St. Bruno's, in Beauval, Saskatchewan, which operated from 1897 to 1995. It was run by the Catholic church. He gave a statement to the Turth and Reconciliation Commission on 24 June 2012 in Saskatoon, Saskatchewan.

name: Doris Young
schoolAttended: Anglican Schools in Manitoba and Saskatchewan
studentBio: Doris Young attended Anglican residential schools in both Manitoba and Saskatchewan. Doris grew up in Northern Manitoba. She gave a statement to the Truth and Reconciliation Commission on 22 June 2012 in Saskatoon, Saskatchewan.

name: Delores Adolph
studentBio: Delores Adolph attended the residential school in Mission, British Columbia likely called St. Mary's sometime in the 1950s. The school was operated by the Catholic church from 1867 to 1984. Delores gave a statement to the Truth and Reconciliation Commission on 19 May 2011 in Mission, British Columbia

name: Martha Loon
studentBio: Martha Loon attended Poplar Hill Residential School at Poplar Hill, Ontario in the 1980s. The school was Mennonite-operated. Martha gave a statement to the Truth and Reconciliation Commission on 25 Novemeber 2010 in Thunder Bay, Ontario.

name: Richard Hall
studentBio: Richard Hall first attended the residential school in Port Alberni, British Columbia in the 1950s when he was twelve years old. The school was operated by the Presbyterian church and closed in 1973. Richard gave a statement to the Turth and Reconciliation Commission on 18 September 2013 in Vancouver, British Columbia.

name: Noel Starblanket
studentBio: Noel Starblanket attended Lebret Residential School at Fort Qu'Appelle, Saskatchewan. The school was open from 1884 until 1998 and was operated by the Catholic church. Noel gave a statement to the Truth and Reconciliation Commission on 16 January 2012 in Regina, Saskatchewan.

name: Patrick James Hall
studentBio: Patrick James Hall attended the Brandon Residential School in Brandon, Manitoba in the 1960s or 1970s. The school was run by the Methodist United Catholic church from 895 until 1972. Patrick gave a statement to the Truth and Reconciliation Commission on 21 December 2010 in Winnipeg, Manitoba.

name: Isaac Daniels
studentBio: Isaac Daniels left home in 1945 and attended a school in Prince Albert, Saskatchewan run by the Anglican church. He gave a statement to the Truth and Reconciliation Commission on 22 June 2012 in Saskatoon, Saskatchewan.

name: Donna Antoine
studentBio: Donna Antoine attended residential schools in British Columbia run by the Roman Catholic church. She gave a statement to the Truth and Reconciliation Commission on 13 October 2011 in Enderby, British Columbia.
